flavor_text_entries.diamond:
Small Pokémon occasionally gather
on its unmoving back to begin
building their nests.
flavor_text_entries.pearl:
Groups of this Pokémon migrating
in search of water have been
mistaken for “moving forests.”
flavor_text_entries.platinum:
Some Pokémon are born on a
TORTERRA’s back and spend their
entire life there.
flavor_text_entries.heartgold:
Ancient people imagined that
beneath the ground, a gigantic
TORTERRA dwelled.

flavor_text_entries.legends-arceus:
This remarkable, large-bodied Pokémon would serve beautifully
as borrowed scenery for a garden, and its strength is peerless.
Torterra roams the wilderness in search of clean water.
